Shopping List Suggestions

Seeds and plants
- Tomato seeds/starts: Plum Regal, Juliet, Viva Italia, Sungold, Cherry 100 (8–10 plants)  
- Basil seeds/starts: 12 plants  
- Okra seeds: enough for 4–5 plants  
- Eggplant starts: 2 plants  
- Bush bean seed: enough for 60–80 plants  
- Potato seed pieces: ~10–12 pieces  
- Carrot seed: small packet for 30–40 carrots  
- Alpine strawberry transplants: 55–65 plants (you already have seedlings)  
- Corn seed: 16 seeds for 4×4 block (if using)  
- Watermelon seed/plant: 1 vigorous plant

Irrigation
- 1/2" mainline tubing × length for two beds  
- 1 GPH emitters × ~100 (spare)  
- Soaker hose for beans and carrots × 2 beds  
- Pressure regulator 15–20 PSI  
- Timer/controller

Soil and fertility
- Compost (enough to add 2 in to both beds)  
- Balanced organic fertilizer for side‑dressing  
- Lime or gypsum if soil test indicates need for calcium

Support and protection
- Tomato cages or stakes × 10  
- Mulch (straw or shredded leaves)  
- Row cover fabric for early season pest protection

---

Appendix: Quick Reference — Plant Effects on Soil

- Beans (legumes): fix atmospheric nitrogen via root nodules; improve soil N for following crops.  
- Corn & Potatoes: heavy feeders; remove significant N and other nutrients; follow with compost or legumes.  
- Tomatoes & Eggplant: heavy feeders; benefit from compost and side‑dressing; susceptible to blight if rotated poorly.  
- Carrots & Strawberries: light to moderate feeders; strawberries prefer slightly lower pH.

